# Color Scheme — "Atelier"

An editorial light/dark palette: warm neutral base with a refined plum accent.
Tokens are defined once in `frontend/src/app/globals.css` as OKLCH CSS variables
and exposed to Tailwind via `@theme inline`. They are shadcn/ui compatible.

## Golden rule: use semantic tokens, never raw colors

Style with the semantic utilities below. NEVER hardcode a color scale
(`zinc-900`, `gray-100`, `bg-white`, `#0a0a0a`, `text-red-600`, …) and NEVER
sprinkle `dark:` variants for color — the tokens already switch with the theme.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — semantic, theme-aware, no dark: needed
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
  <button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90" />
  <p className="text-muted-foreground" />
  <span className="border border-border" />
</div>

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded scales + manual dark: variants
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-black text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
  <button className="bg-zinc-900 dark:bg-zinc-100 text-white dark:text-zinc-900" />
</div>
```

## Available tokens

| Utility (bg-/text-/border-)          | Use for                                   |
|--------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| `background` / `foreground`          | Page surface and default text             |
| `card` / `card-foreground`           | Raised panels, sheets, modals             |
| `popover` / `popover-foreground`     | Floating menus, popovers, tooltips        |
| `primary` / `primary-foreground`     | Primary actions, emphasis (the plum)      |
| `secondary` / `secondary-foreground` | Secondary buttons, subtle fills           |
| `muted` / `muted-foreground`         | Muted backgrounds and de-emphasized text  |
| `accent` / `accent-foreground`       | Hover states, highlights                  |
| `destructive` / `destructive-foreground` | Errors, delete/danger actions         |
| `border`, `input`, `ring`            | Borders, input borders, focus rings       |

Radius: use `rounded-sm|md|lg|xl` (driven by the `--radius` token) for
consistency; pill controls stay `rounded-full`.

- `*-foreground` is the text/icon color that sits **on top of** its base
  (e.g. `text-primary-foreground` on `bg-primary`).
- Adjust opacity inline for hover/disabled: `bg-primary/90`, `border-border/60`.

## Dark mode

Dark mode is **class-based**: the `.dark` class on `<html>` swaps the token
values (see the `.dark` block and `@custom-variant dark` in `globals.css`).
Because components use semantic tokens, they adapt with zero extra markup — do
NOT scatter `dark:` color variants through components.

The theme is controlled by a dependency-free switcher:

- An inline script in `src/app/layout.tsx` applies the persisted choice
  (`localStorage.theme`) or the system preference before first paint (no FOUC).
  `<html>` has `suppressHydrationWarning` because the script mutates its class.
- `src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` (a `role="switch"` button) flips the `.dark`
  class and persists the choice to `localStorage.theme`.

Theme preference in `localStorage` is fine — but per the BFF auth rule, NEVER
put tokens or credentials there.

## Changing the palette

Edit only the CSS variables in `frontend/src/app/globals.css` (the `:root` and
`prefers-color-scheme: dark` blocks). Never redefine colors in components.
Keep new colors in OKLCH and provide both a light and a dark value. When shadcn
components are added, they consume these same tokens automatically.
